oint pain and swelling. The high fiber content in Brassica oleracea proles napobrassica also aids in managing blood sugar levels, making it beneficial for individuals with diabetes. Additionally, its rich content of vitamins and minerals, particularly vitamin C and potassium, helps to alleviate symptoms of scurvy and hypertension. Furthermore, its antiseptic properties can be used to treat skin conditions like acne and eczema.", "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Brassica oleracea proles napobrassica are isothiocyanates, specifically sulforaphane, which has been shown to have potent anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, and glucosinolates, including glucoraphanin, which is converted to sulforaphane in the body, and glucobrassicin, a precursor to indole-3-carbinol, a compound that has been demonstrated to have anti-cancer and anti-inflammatory effects. Additionally, the vegetable contains kaempferol, a flavonoid with anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, as well as isorhapontigenin, a lignan that has been found to have anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties. The high content of vitamins C and E, along with other essential nutrients, also contributes to its healing properties. The fiber content in napobrassica helps to support digestive health and promote satiety. Furthermore, its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects may also contribute to its potential anti-aging and cardiovascular health benefits.", "properties": [{"name": "antioxidant", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 175, "total_score": 3500}, {"name": "anti-inflammatory", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 169, "total_score": 3380}, {"name": "antimicrobial", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 147, "total_score": 2940}, {"name": "cardioprotective", "mentions": 13, "confidence_score": 87, "total_score": 1131}, {"name": "anticancer", "mentions": 12, "confidence_score": 81, "total_score": 972}, {"name": "analgesic", "mentions": 14, "confidence_scor